I originally started with the Reminder App and after finding it useful, I bought this Pro App to remove the ads. The main benefit with this over Google Calendar is the ringing alarm, i.e. it's not going to make a quick bleep that you'll miss while out of the room. This App certainly grabs my attention, just like a ringing telephone. While individual reminders work fine, repeat reminders are not reliable, an issue that's been ongoing for about 2 years. For example, if the reminder rings and I snooze a reminder for 10 minutes, it doesn't ring after the snooze time, but instead rings 10 minutes after the next repeat reminder time. The repeat reminder also occasionally skips well into the future, which cost me about €50 in out-of-bundle phone charges for forgetting to purchase a new bundle. In this case, it reminded me on the 15th October, but when I checked why it didn't remind me on the 13th November (custom 28 day repeat), it set the next interval to 1st October 2021! So don't use repeat intervals for important reminders.

content: good app, but theres an outstanding bug with widgets not refreshing properly. Devs, please fix it.

Since the 1/29 update, I no longer get any notification sounds. It worked so well before. Update: I figured it out. App Info > App Notification > Importance > High / Importance > Sound > "Select Your Sound"

Update, the Dev listened and agreed to fix what I thought was a major flaw whereby the reminder would update to the next scheduled time based upon the time the reminder was cleared and not from the prescribed subsequent time.  The Dev is pro consumer, welcomes user feedback and is responsive..  At this time I can only give a 2 start rating.  The app will reschedule a repeating alarm for the time past it's scheduled event if you happen to miss the alarm or snooze it. It should reschedule the next event at the time prescribed in the alarm setup.  I have had instances where the alarm did not sound at all and I have had an alarm scheduled for specific days just lose those days and not alert at all.  One of my main reasons for using this type of app is for scheduling financial transactions that can be very costly if missed.  The author has promised to make a change with the delayed time on missed or delayed alarms.  I'll review my rating at such time as that happens.

A "truly intuitive reminder app" is a great way to describe it. One it's best features is the fact that if you copy a chunk of text from another app (maybe an email or text you got that says "Hey, can you take care of this..."), Copy that text, and open Reminder Pro... It'll prompt you to create a new Reminder using what you have in your clipboard. Elegant and intuitive.   Buy the Pro version, it's fantastic.

All the issues I had with the app (on Oreo) have been resolved. Developer is responsive, which is good. I have asked if he can get the Reminder Pro feedback email working as it currently bounces. Also asking for a fortnightly option on the "On Days" repeat option. Simply the best Reminder app for Android I have found so far.

content: I downloaded the free version of this app and rated it 5 stars and thought it was the best reminder app out there.  But..... For the last few weeks most of the time you cannot open the app, it just shuts down immediately.  I made the mistake of paying for the full version thinking it would be ok but it's just as bad.  Reminders still flag up and with the widget I can still add reminders but I can't open the damn app to see my reminders list.  I've reported the problem a couple of times but nothing changes.  Is this a problem for anyone else?  So... Time to bin this and find a more reliable reminder app, which is a shame because this used to be the best.  Update ; After mentioning the problems I was having with the Reminder app the developer has been in touch with me and worked very hard to help me sort the problems out. I can now use the app again and rate it 5 stars. The developer gets 5 stars to for all the effort he has put into helping me.  Many thanks!
